estershire,England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Sibton, Suffolk, England":"Sibton, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hauberk","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Hubert  .","French: from the personal name <i>Aubert</i>, a late medieval form of an ancient Germanic compound name, <i>Adalberht</i> (see   Albert  ).","French: perhaps a metonymic occupational name for someone who made or wore a mailcoat, French <i>haubert</i>, from Old French <i>halberc</i>, <i>hauberc</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Hubert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Armand, Normand, Olivier, Adlore, Alphonse, Andre, Benoit, Camil, Camille, Fernand.","German, Dutch, English, French, Walloon, Breton, Polish, Czech, Slovak, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. The name was borne by an 8th-century Christian saint, bishop of Maastricht, who was adopted as the patron of hunters, and helped to increase the popularity of the personal name, especially in the Low Countries.","History: Jean-François-Barthélemi Hubert from Granville in Manche, France, married Félicité Arsenault in Havre-Aubert, QC, in 1801. Nicolas Hubert <i>dit</i> Lacroix from France married Marguerite Landreau in France <i>c.</i> 1653, died in Montreal, QC, in 1687. René Hubert from Paris, France, married Françoise (de) Lacroix in Quebec City, QC, in 1669. Pierre-Paul Hébert/Hubert from France married Suzanne Laporte in QC <i>c.</i> 1716. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of South Carolina."]}]},{"name":"Gervas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Possibly Germanic.  See  <b>Gervaise</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gervas Hawberk Hauberk was born about 1270, in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Simon Hauberk II  Lord of Scaldford and Unknown. He had at least 6 sons with Agnes Wecheham Wykham. He died after 1343, in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1270–after 1343":"umbes 1270–pärast 1343","1270–1343":"1270–1343","–1344":"–1344","–Male":"Surnud","1270–1401":"1270–1401","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1358–1396":"1358–1396","–1395":"–1395","–1411":"–1411","–1417":"–1417","1250–1330":"1250–1330","–Female":"Surnud","about 1270":"umbes 1270","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1330":"1330","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1348":"1348","1358":"1358","1401":"1401","1411":"1411","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","after 1330":"pärast 1330","after 1343":"pärast 1343","1417":"1417","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sacldford,Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Heredby, Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sibton, Suffolk, England":"Sibton, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1270–after 1343":"noin 1270–1343 jälkeen","1270–1343":"1270–1343","–1344":"–1344","–Male":"Kuollut","1270–1401":"1270–1401","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1358–1396":"1358–1396","–1395":"–1395","–1411":"–1411","–1417":"–1417","1250–1330":"1250–1330","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1270":"noin 1270","about 1290":"noin 1290","1330":"1330","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1348":"1348","1358":"1358","1401":"1401","1411":"1411","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","after 1330":"1330 jälkeen","after 1343":"1343 jälkeen","1417":"1417","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sacldford,Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Heredby, Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sibton, Suffolk,